race.comment: SHOCKSTAR (3) is close to breaking through after two consecutive placings, the latest coming when second over 2010m at Kilmore. Maps well and is well-placed in this lineup. Top chance. MARLIN (1) missed a whisker this track/trip and then skipped across to Adelaide and didn't get warm in a 63 at big odds. This suits better, and on a 3-week return he can make the finish. HAND OF DOOM (2) comes back in trip off the Maiden win at Moe, where he led them up. Has a low gate and will give a sight at decent odds. SUNSET MISSILE (6) would be a chance at best but she has to find it as would SMOKIN' GIANT (8).
